[5] Diarrhea - South Africa (N. Cape)
Date: Tue, 24 May 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: SundayTimes.co.za [edited]
http://www.sundaytimes.co.za/zones/sundaytimesNEW/newsst/newsst1116928168.asp



Diarrhea outbreak
-----------------
Health officials are monitoring a diarrhea outbreak in Postmasburg in
the Northern Cape after more than 100 people reported to clinics with
severe symptoms. According to local media, 104 cases have been
reported so far.

The Northern Cape health department said stool and water samples from
boreholes and taps in various townships in the Postmasburg area had
been collected and sent for testing. The department is awaiting the
results.

Health officials in the meantime distributed pamphlets in the area,
advising people to boil water before they drink it, and cautioning
children to wash their hands after using the toilet.

The department's Outbreak Response Team is monitoring the situation.

--
